Fast-rising Afropop artiste, Charles Chibueze Chukwu, known as Crayon, has said Grammy award-winning Wizkid inspired him to walk the musical career path. Crayon, whose breakthrough single “So Fine” shot him to the limelight, made this known on social media after a fan, Ibrahim Khalil, quizzed him to know the musician that inspired him to do music. Khalil wrote: “#askcray which musician inspired you to do music?” In his response, the singer who is signed under Baby Fresh’s Blowtime Entertainment, an imprint of Mavin Records noted he got inspired to do music after watching Big Wiz on television.   Bobrisky begs billionaires to patronise his ‘market’     Fans rejoice as MC Oluomo reconciles Iyabo Ojo, Faithia…     Tobi Bakre: My wife’s ‘legwork’ stole my heart   - Advertisement - The 21-year-old singer also said he informed his mom at the time that he wanted to be Wizkid’s replica. He wrote: “When I saw Wizkid on tv, I legit told my mom I want to be like him! “Back in 2011 Superstar album was the first album I bought with my hard-earned money. “I bought the album in traffic at Iyanaiba! “Now that I’m an artist, I feel so bad to have bought that album for that amount tbh (to be honest).”